      • insertEventInDB

        public static void insertEventInDB(java.lang.String key,
                                   java.lang.String val1,
                                   java.lang.String val2,
                                   java.lang.String val3)
        This method will insert event and its params into DB
        Parameters:
        key - - event id
        val1 - - event params
        val2 - - event params
        val3 - - event params

        The DB column names and the param names are all intentionally kept generic. That way this mechanism need not be tied to a particular scenario. The additional params like val2 and val3 can be unused. For now, we are using this to pass on the messageid of the message received on GCM from a new contact. Later when the contact is rcvd from SSE as add friend, this table will be used to pick the latest messageid for that newly added contact.
